    "end": "62320"
  },
  {
    "text": "functionalities of the feature",
    "start": "62320",
    "end": "65040"
  },
  {
    "text": "then we will talk about what we are",
    "start": "65040",
    "end": "67280"
  },
  {
    "text": "working on in kubernetes 1.23 release to",
    "start": "67280",
    "end": "71520"
  },
  {
    "text": "improve this feature",
    "start": "71520",
    "end": "73520"
  },
  {
    "text": "and finally we will talk about",
    "start": "73520",
    "end": "75840"
  },
  {
    "text": "what we are planning to do",
    "start": "75840",
    "end": "77600"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the future",
    "start": "77600",
    "end": "80320"
  },
  {
    "text": "so",
    "start": "83200",
    "end": "85280"
  },
  {
    "text": "let's see what could happen to your",
    "start": "85280",
    "end": "86799"
  },
  {
    "text": "volume after it is provisioned",
    "start": "86799",
    "end": "90240"
  },
  {
    "text": "as shown here we have an application",
    "start": "90240",
    "end": "93360"
  },
  {
    "text": "running",
    "start": "93360",
    "end": "94400"
  },
  {
    "text": "using a c4 set with three replicas",
    "start": "94400",
    "end": "98640"
  },
  {
    "text": "it has three parts",
    "start": "98640",
    "end": "101040"
  },
  {
    "text": "each is using a pvc",
    "start": "101040",
    "end": "104399"
  },
  {
    "text": "everything looks perfect for a while",
    "start": "104399",
    "end": "107360"
  },
  {
    "text": "but then one day something happened",
    "start": "107360",
    "end": "111360"
  },
  {
    "text": "an admin",
    "start": "111360",
    "end": "112640"
  },
  {
    "text": "was working on something and made a",
    "start": "112640",
    "end": "115119"
  },
  {
    "text": "mistake by accident",
    "start": "115119",
    "end": "117280"
  },
  {
    "text": "and as a result the volume was deleted",
    "start": "117280",
    "end": "120399"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the study system",
    "start": "120399",
    "end": "123439"
  },
  {
    "text": "in any case the admin didn't realize",
    "start": "123600",
    "end": "126560"
  },
  {
    "text": "that he or she did something wrong that",
    "start": "126560",
    "end": "128879"
  },
  {
    "text": "could affect applications running on the",
    "start": "128879",
    "end": "131599"
  },
  {
    "text": "platform",
    "start": "131599",
    "end": "133120"
  },
  {
    "text": "so",
    "start": "133120",
    "end": "133920"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the surface",
    "start": "133920",
    "end": "135440"
  },
  {
    "text": "everything looked fine",
    "start": "135440",
    "end": "137599"
  },
  {
    "text": "because kubernetes does not check what",
    "start": "137599",
    "end": "140239"
  },
  {
    "text": "happened to the underlying volume on the",
    "start": "140239",
    "end": "142720"
  },
  {
    "text": "study system",
    "start": "142720",
    "end": "144080"
  },
  {
    "text": "after it is provisioned and used by a",
    "start": "144080",
    "end": "147120"
  },
  {
    "text": "pod",
    "start": "147120",
    "end": "149120"
  },
  {
    "text": "everything looked normal",
    "start": "149120",
    "end": "150959"
  },
  {
    "text": "until when the application tried to",
    "start": "150959",
    "end": "153360"
  },
  {
    "text": "write to the volume",
    "start": "153360",
    "end": "155519"
  },
  {
    "text": "then of course",
    "start": "155519",
    "end": "157120"
  },
  {
    "text": "it failed",
    "start": "157120",
    "end": "159200"
  },
  {
    "text": "now the user tried to figure out what",
    "start": "159200",
    "end": "161680"
  },
  {
    "text": "happened by checking the logs",
    "start": "161680",
    "end": "164160"
  },
  {
    "text": "but there are no clear messages that",
    "start": "164160",
    "end": "166560"
  },
  {
    "text": "indicate the volume was deleted",
    "start": "166560",
    "end": "170239"
  },
  {
    "text": "so the user opened the ticket with the",
    "start": "170239",
    "end": "173120"
  },
  {
    "text": "infrastructure team",
    "start": "173120",
    "end": "174959"
  },
  {
    "text": "then the infrastructure team started to",
    "start": "174959",
    "end": "177440"
  },
  {
    "text": "troubleshoot the problem",
    "start": "177440",
    "end": "180000"
  },
  {
    "text": "it is not easy for them to root cause",
    "start": "180000",
    "end": "182239"
  },
  {
    "text": "the problem either as there isn't enough",
    "start": "182239",
    "end": "185599"
  },
  {
    "text": "information in the logs",
    "start": "185599",
    "end": "188560"
  },
  {
    "text": "so it's going to take a while for the",
    "start": "188560",
    "end": "190400"
  },
  {
    "text": "real problem to be discovered",
    "start": "190400",
    "end": "194319"
  },
  {
    "text": "there are other possible failures as",
    "start": "195440",
    "end": "197200"
  },
  {
    "text": "well",
    "start": "197200",
    "end": "199840"
  },
  {
    "text": "the admin may have removed the disk for",
    "start": "200319",
    "end": "203599"
  },
  {
    "text": "maintenance or replacement without",
    "start": "203599",
    "end": "206480"
  },
  {
    "text": "knowing that it has an impact to the",
    "start": "206480",
    "end": "209040"
  },
  {
    "text": "running applications",
    "start": "209040",
    "end": "212439"
  },
  {
    "text": "the disk that the warning resides on",
    "start": "213040",
    "end": "215519"
  },
  {
    "text": "could fail",
    "start": "215519",
    "end": "218159"
  },
  {
    "text": "there may be configuration issues with",
    "start": "219440",
    "end": "221760"
  },
  {
    "text": "down the lines for the system that",
    "start": "221760",
    "end": "223760"
  },
  {
    "text": "affect the volumes health",
    "start": "223760",
    "end": "227840"
  },
  {
    "text": "the volume could be out of capacity so",
    "start": "228799",
    "end": "232080"
  },
  {
    "text": "app can no longer write the volume until",
    "start": "232080",
    "end": "234959"
  },
  {
    "text": "the voting is expanded",
    "start": "234959",
    "end": "238080"
  },
  {
    "text": "the disk may be degrading which affects",
    "start": "239599",
    "end": "242799"
  },
  {
    "text": "its performance",
    "start": "242799",
    "end": "245599"
  },
  {
    "text": "there are other possible",
    "start": "248159",
    "end": "250000"
  },
  {
    "text": "problems that could happen to the volume",
    "start": "250000",
    "end": "252480"
  },
  {
    "text": "after it is provisioned and used by a",
    "start": "252480",
    "end": "254799"
  },
  {
    "text": "pod",
    "start": "254799",
    "end": "257120"
  },
  {
    "text": "for local volumes",
    "start": "257280",
    "end": "259120"
  },
  {
    "text": "if that node where the local volumes",
    "start": "259120",
    "end": "261600"
  },
  {
    "text": "resides fails",
    "start": "261600",
    "end": "263520"
  },
  {
    "text": "the volume also does not exist anymore",
    "start": "263520",
    "end": "268599"
  },
  {
    "text": "let me be rewrite io errors",
    "start": "268800",
    "end": "272880"
  },
  {
    "text": "the file system on the volume may be",
    "start": "272880",
    "end": "275360"
  },
  {
    "text": "corrupted",
    "start": "275360",
    "end": "277040"
  },
  {
    "text": "the file system",
    "start": "277040",
    "end": "278479"
  },
  {
    "text": "may be out of capacity",
    "start": "278479",
    "end": "281680"
  },
  {
    "text": "volume may be outmounted by accident",
    "start": "281680",
    "end": "284960"
  },
  {
    "text": "outside of kubernetes",
    "start": "284960",
    "end": "288080"
  },
  {
    "text": "there could be other issues that are not",
    "start": "288080",
    "end": "290000"
  },
  {
    "text": "captured here",
    "start": "290000",
    "end": "292000"
  },
  {
    "text": "so how do we solve these problems and",
    "start": "292000",
    "end": "295120"
  },
  {
    "text": "improve user experience",
    "start": "295120",
    "end": "298479"
  },
  {
    "text": "to solve this problem we introduced an",
    "start": "300960",
    "end": "304000"
  },
  {
    "text": "other feature called volume health",
    "start": "304000",
    "end": "306400"
  },
  {
    "text": "monitoring",
    "start": "306400",
    "end": "309039"
  },
  {
    "text": "without warning house monitoring",
    "start": "309360",
    "end": "311440"
  },
  {
    "text": "kubernetes has no knowledge of what",
    "start": "311440",
    "end": "313680"
  },
  {
    "text": "happened to the underlying volumes on",
    "start": "313680",
    "end": "316000"
  },
  {
    "text": "the study system",
    "start": "316000",
    "end": "317520"
  },
  {
    "text": "after a pvc is provisioned and used by a",
    "start": "317520",
    "end": "320560"
  },
  {
    "text": "pod",
    "start": "320560",
    "end": "321919"
  },
  {
    "text": "with this feature",
    "start": "321919",
    "end": "323280"
  },
  {
    "text": "csi driver can communicate with solid",
    "start": "323280",
    "end": "326000"
  },
  {
    "text": "systems and find out what happens to the",
    "start": "326000",
    "end": "329039"
  },
  {
    "text": "volumes and communicate back to",
    "start": "329039",
    "end": "331280"
  },
  {
    "text": "kubernetes",
    "start": "331280",
    "end": "332720"
  },
  {
    "text": "so kubernetes can report events on pvcs",
    "start": "332720",
    "end": "336639"
  },
  {
    "text": "or pods if volume conditions become",
    "start": "336639",
    "end": "340400"
  },
  {
    "text": "abnormal",
    "start": "340400",
    "end": "343039"
  },
  {
    "text": "this feature includes two parts",
    "start": "343440",
    "end": "347600"
  },
  {
    "text": "there is an external boiling house",
    "start": "347840",
    "end": "350000"
  },
  {
    "text": "monitoring controller",
    "start": "350000",
    "end": "351759"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is a side car deployed with the csr",
    "start": "351759",
    "end": "354880"
  },
  {
    "text": "driver to monitor volume health from the",
    "start": "354880",
    "end": "358000"
  },
  {
    "text": "controller side",
    "start": "358000",
    "end": "360160"
  },
  {
    "text": "it reports events to the pvc when",
    "start": "360160",
    "end": "363120"
  },
  {
    "text": "abnormal condition is detected",
    "start": "363120",
    "end": "367479"
  },
  {
    "text": "cubelet also monitors warning health",
    "start": "368400",
    "end": "371120"
  },
  {
    "text": "from the node side",
    "start": "371120",
    "end": "373039"
  },
  {
    "text": "it reports events to the pod when",
    "start": "373039",
    "end": "375919"
  },
  {
    "text": "abnormal warning condition is detected",
    "start": "375919",
    "end": "380680"
  },
  {
    "text": "so here we have a csi deployment example",
    "start": "384080",
    "end": "387919"
  },
  {
    "text": "that shows",
    "start": "387919",
    "end": "389199"
  },
  {
    "text": "various kubernetes components",
    "start": "389199",
    "end": "392000"
  },
  {
    "text": "the csi driver",
    "start": "392000",
    "end": "393600"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the storage system that is used to",
    "start": "393600",
    "end": "396319"
  },
  {
    "text": "persist the data on the volumes",
    "start": "396319",
    "end": "400000"
  },
  {
    "text": "here we have cube controller manager on",
    "start": "400000",
    "end": "402880"
  },
  {
    "text": "the master node",
    "start": "402880",
    "end": "404560"
  },
  {
    "text": "see that driver controller plugin",
    "start": "404560",
    "end": "407360"
  },
